description: Create or update a phone number rule override and associate it with a protect configuration.

parameters.name: ClientToken
parameters.description: Unique, case-sensitive identifier that you provide to ensure the idempotency of the request. If you don't specify a client token, a randomly generated token is used for the request to ensure idempotency. This field is autopopulated if not provided.

parameters.name: ProtectConfigurationId
parameters.description: The unique identifier for the protect configuration.

parameters.name: DestinationPhoneNumber
parameters.description: The destination phone number in E.164 format.

parameters.name: Action
parameters.description: The action for the rule to either block or allow messages to the destination phone number.

nested_items.name: ProtectConfigurationArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the protect configuration.

nested_items.name: ProtectConfigurationId
nested_items.description: The unique identifier for the protect configuration.

nested_items.name: DestinationPhoneNumber
nested_items.description: The destination phone number in E.164 format.

nested_items.name: CreatedTimestamp
nested_items.description: The time when the rule was created, in UNIX epoch time format.

nested_items.name: Action
nested_items.description: The action for the rule to take.

nested_items.name: IsoCountryCode
nested_items.description: The two-character code, in ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 format, for the country or region.

nested_items.name: ExpirationTimestamp
nested_items.description: The time the rule will expire at.
